# CaritasApp - Charity Shop Ledger Web App Plan

## 1) Product goal
Build a simple, secure web app connected to Supabase so a charity shop manager can:
- Track volunteer hours
- Track daily cash movements in the shop
- Track manual bank account ledger entries (deposits and extractions)
- Attach receipt photos to transactions when needed
- Sign in with Google (via Supabase Auth)

No direct bank API integration is required for MVP. The bank area is a manual ledger.

## 2) Suggested MVP stack
- Frontend: Next.js (App Router) + TypeScript
- UI: Tailwind CSS + a lightweight component library (optional)
- Backend: Supabase (Postgres, Auth, Storage, RLS)
- Forms/validation: React Hook Form + Zod
- Deployment: Vercel (frontend) + Supabase project

## 3) Roles and access
- **Manager/Admin**
  - Full access to volunteers, cash ledger, bank ledger, receipts, reports
- **Volunteer**
  - Can log own hours
  - Can view own submitted hours
  - No financial editing by default
- **Accountant (optional)**
  - Read-only access to finance pages and exports

## 4) Data model (MVP)

### `profiles`
Linked to `auth.users`.
- `id uuid` (PK, references auth user id)
- `full_name text`
- `email text`
- `created_at timestamptz`

### `shops`
Supports one or many shops.
- `id uuid` (PK)
- `name text`
- `currency text` (for example `EUR`)
- `timezone text`

### `user_shop_roles`
Membership and role per shop.
- `id uuid` (PK)
- `user_id uuid` (FK -> profiles.id)
- `shop_id uuid` (FK -> shops.id)
- `role text` (`manager`, `volunteer`, `accountant`)

### `volunteer_hours`
- `id uuid` (PK)
- `shop_id uuid` (FK)
- `user_id uuid` (FK)
- `work_date date`
- `start_time time`
- `end_time time`
- `hours numeric(5,2)` (can be auto-calculated)
- `notes text`
- `status text` (`submitted`, `approved`, `rejected`)
- `approved_by uuid` (nullable)
- `created_at timestamptz`

### `cash_sessions`
One row per day (or shift) to support opening/closing checks.
- `id uuid` (PK)
- `shop_id uuid` (FK)
- `session_date date`
- `opening_cash numeric(12,2)`
- `closing_cash_counted numeric(12,2)` (nullable until close)
- `notes text`
- `closed_by uuid` (nullable)
- `closed_at timestamptz` (nullable)

### `cash_entries`
Every cash movement in the shop.
- `id uuid` (PK)
- `shop_id uuid` (FK)
- `cash_session_id uuid` (FK)
- `entry_date timestamptz`
- `type text` (`sale`, `expense`, `float_in`, `float_out`, `deposit_to_bank`, `adjustment`)
- `direction text` (`in`, `out`)
- `category text`
- `amount numeric(12,2)` (positive only)
- `description text`
- `created_by uuid`
- `created_at timestamptz`

### `bank_ledger_entries`
Manual ledger for the real bank account.
- `id uuid` (PK)
- `shop_id uuid` (FK)
- `entry_date timestamptz`
- `type text` (`cash_deposit`, `withdrawal`, `bank_fee`, `adjustment`, `other`)
- `direction text` (`in`, `out`)
- `amount numeric(12,2)` (positive only)
- `reference text` (deposit slip id, note, etc.)
- `description text`
- `created_by uuid`
- `created_at timestamptz`

### `receipts`
Metadata for uploaded images.
- `id uuid` (PK)
- `shop_id uuid` (FK)
- `entity_type text` (`cash_entry`, `bank_entry`)
- `entity_id uuid`
- `storage_path text`
- `uploaded_by uuid`
- `created_at timestamptz`

## 5) Storage plan for receipt photos
- Supabase Storage bucket: `receipts`
- Path convention: `shop/{shop_id}/{entity_type}/{entity_id}/{timestamp}.jpg`
- Restrict access via storage policies:
  - Managers can upload/read all receipts in their shop
  - Volunteers can upload receipts only when creating allowed records
- Validate file type and max size in frontend and backend

## 6) Security and audit requirements
- Enable RLS on every app table
- Scope all finance and hours data by `shop_id`
- Derive permissions from `user_shop_roles`
- Add `created_by`, `created_at`, and optional `updated_at`
- Avoid hard deletion for financial records (prefer reversal/correction entries)
- Keep financial amounts positive and use `direction` for sign logic

## 7) Main screens (MVP)
1. **Sign in**
   - Google OAuth through Supabase Auth
2. **Dashboard**
   - Today's cash in/out totals
   - Current cash session status
   - Pending volunteer hours approvals
3. **Volunteer Hours**
   - Log shift
   - List/filter by date and volunteer
   - Approve/reject (manager)
4. **Cash Ledger**
   - Open/close daily session
   - Add cash entries
   - Running daily total
5. **Bank Ledger**
   - Add deposit/extraction entries
   - Filter by date/type
   - Running balance view
6. **Receipts**
   - Upload image for a cash or bank entry
   - Preview/download
7. **Reports**
   - CSV export for selected date ranges

## 8) Business rules to implement early
- Only one open `cash_session` per shop per day
- `end_time` must be after `start_time` for volunteer hours
- `hours` auto-calculated, with manual override only for managers
- `amount > 0` for all finance entries
- No edits on closed/reconciled sessions unless manager overrides
- Corrections should be separate entries, not destructive edits

## 9) Delivery phases

### Phase 1 - Foundation
- Create Supabase project
- Configure Google OAuth provider
- Add initial SQL migrations for tables + indexes + RLS
- Seed one shop and one manager

### Phase 2 - Core workflows
- Build auth/session handling in Next.js
- Build Volunteer Hours CRUD + approvals
- Build Cash Sessions + Cash Entries
- Build Bank Ledger Entries

### Phase 3 - Receipts and reporting
- Add receipt upload + linking
- Add dashboard summaries
- Add CSV exports

### Phase 4 - Hardening
- Validation and error handling
- Audit trails and correction flow
- E2E smoke tests
- Basic backup/restore runbook

## 10) Suggested initial backlog
- [ ] Set up Next.js app and Supabase client
- [ ] Create migration 001 (core tables)
- [ ] Create migration 002 (RLS policies)
- [ ] Implement Google login flow
- [ ] Build Volunteer Hours page
- [ ] Build Cash Ledger page
- [ ] Build Bank Ledger page
- [ ] Implement receipt uploads
- [ ] Add dashboard aggregates
- [ ] Add CSV export endpoints

## 11) Open decisions
- Single shop or multi-shop at launch?
- Final currency and timezone defaults?
- Who can approve volunteer hours?
- Do you need monthly lock/reconciliation for finance data?
- Should volunteers see finance summaries or only managers?

## 12) Definition of done for MVP
MVP is done when a manager can sign in with Google, record volunteer hours, record daily cash and bank ledger movements, attach receipts, and export data - with RLS enforcing that users only access data they are allowed to see.
